HEADWORD: Copulatory
<hw>Cop"u*la*to*ry</hw> <pr>(k⟦ocr⟧p"⟦usl⟧*l⟦adot⟧*t⟦osl⟧*r⟦ycr⟧)</pr>,
<pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Pertaining to copulation; tending or
serving to unite; copulative.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Used in sexual union; <as>as, the
<ex>copulatory</ex> organs of insects</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

